useTypoMetrics

If the hhea metrics match the sTypo metrics and not usWin metrics the fsSelection useTypoMetrics flag should be True.

WWS

'OS/2' fsSelection flag for WWS should be True but is False.

Asap Condensed Regular (AsapCondensed-Regular.ttf)

OS/2

italic flag

'OS/2' fsSelection italic flag should match the 'head' macStyle italic flag. They should be the same.

OK: They are the same.'OS/2' fsSelection italic flag is False and 'head' macStyle italic flag is False.

Asap Condensed Regular (AsapCondensed-Regular.ttf)

OS/2

Panose Normal

Because 'OS/2' fsSelection italic flag is False and 'head' macStyle italic flag is False the OS/2 panose array form flag should be a 'Normal' entry.

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Asap Condensed Italic (AsapCondensed-Italic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'AsapCondensed-Italic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Asap Condensed Italic (AsapCondensed-Italic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'AsapCondensed-Italic', Everything looks good.

Asap Condensed Medium Regular (AsapCondensed-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Asap Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Asap Condensed Medium'.

Asap Condensed Medium Italic (AsapCondensed-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Asap Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Asap Condensed Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Asap Condensed SemiBold Regular (AsapCondensed-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'AsapCondensed-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

MS NID 16/17

NID 16 'Asap Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Asap Condensed SemiBold'.

Asap Condensed SemiBold Italic (AsapCondensed-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Asap Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Asap Condensed SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Asap Condensed Bold (AsapCondensed-Bold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'AsapCondensed-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Asap Condensed Bold (AsapCondensed-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'AsapCondensed-Bold', Everything looks good.
